             <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="purley"></a>Purley Festival 26 June - 2 July</h3>
                <p>Purley Festival is back from 26 June to 2 July 2017<p>
                <p><%= link_to "Visit the Purley Festival website for full details of all the events", "http://www.purleyfestival.co.uk/" %></p>
                <p>After a year off we are back with lots of renewed energy, ideas and new members of the team. Purley Festival has its roots firmly planted in the community and it is local people and their ideas that make the Festival so exciting – no year is the same!</p><p>Everyone knows we put on a week long Festival with a mega two day Finale but not many people know about our Charity work and volunteer mentoring scheme. We are very proud that this year’s charity partners are the South East Cancer Help Centre and Marie Curie and they will be around at the Finale weekend so please give generously to their vital work.</p>
              </td>
              <td class="events"><h3><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/PF_logo2017_100.png", alt: "Purley Festival logo"), "http://www.purleyfestival.co.uk/" %></h3>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="running"></a>Jubilee Running, 10k Fun Run. Sunday 2nd July, starting at 9.30 am</h3>
                <p>Runners and walkers welcome. A slightly undulating 10k multi-terrain course encompassing the local areas of Selsdon, Sanderstead and Warlingham.</p>
                <p>Entrants must be 15 years of age. Entrance fees: UKA Affiliated Runner £10.00, Non-Affiliated Runner (Please add a further £2.00 for Race Day entry, subject to availability). Proceeds go to the British Heart foundation.</p>
                <p>For an entry form, please contact the Jubilee Church office on
                020 8651 2807, e-mail office@croydon-Jubilee.co.uk or enquire in person at Race HQ: Selsdon Hall, 132 Addington Road, Selsdon CR2 8LA</p>
              </td>
              <td class="events"><h3><%= link_to image_tag("small-images/jubilee100.jpg", alt: "Jubilee logo"), "resource/jubilee_running.pdf" %></h3>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="singing"></a>Soul Symphony Choir Open rehearsals 4, 11 and 18th July and 12 September</h3>
                <p>Sould Symphony Choir raises money for good causes including "Mind" in Croydon. If you want to join the group and help raise money for local causes, Joanne is holding a free ‘open rehearsal’ on Tuesdays, 4-18 in July 2017 and 12 September at 7.30pm at The Holy Family Church Hall, 115 Limpsfield Road CR2 9LF. Next concert Sunday 23 July 2017, joanne@soulsymphony.co.uk</p>
                <p><%= link_to "Find out more about Soul Symphony Choir", "resource/singing.pdf" %>.</p>
              </td>
              <td class="events"><h3><%= link_to "Soul Symphony Choir", "resource/singing.pdf"  %></h3>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="farley"></a>Farley Road Practice, Open Meeting. Thursday 20th July</h3>
                <p>Farley Road Medical Practice Patient Participation Group Open Meeting Thursday 20th July.</p>
                <p>We are holding an Open Meeting on 20th July 2017 from 6.30 until 8pm at the Selsdon Centre for the Retired (next to Sainsbury and the Library). Come and talk to the Practice and Patient Participation Group members to learn about the way the Practice works.  Contribute your ideas to improve the Practice.</p>
                <p>RSVP to reserve your place to Ms Tracy Ford, Practice Manager on admin@farleymedical.info or call 020 8651 1222 and leave your details.</p>
              </td>
              <td class="events"><h3><%= link_to "Farley Rd Practice", "resource/Farley_rd_open.pdf"  %></h3>
              </td>
            </tr>

